node.title: Scientists are studying whether Omicron leads to severe illness.
node.description: Should the Omicron variant cause severe illness, that will become apparent if there is a significant rise in hospitalizations over the next week or two, one expert said.

node.title: Whincup to adopt trademark 'win it or bin it' attitude in Bathurst 1000 farewell
node.description: It what will be his final appearance as a Supercars driver, Jamie Whincup is aiming to conquer the Mount Panorama Circuit for a fifth time to cap off his remarkable career behind the wheel.

node.title: A Melbourne supermarket racially profiled African customers for three years. Now it's apologising
node.description: An IGA store in Melbourne apologises for displaying a sign encouraging staff to seek extra assistance when African people entered the store.

node.title: Albanese says Omicron reinforces case for purpose-built quarantine over hotels
node.description: The arrival of the new COVID-19 "variant of concern" has revived the political debate over quarantine ahead of a national cabinet meeting on Tuesday.
